Removal of adhesive strips (e.g., after wound dressings or procedures) is typically simple and can be safely performed by the patient at home, provided they follow basic hygiene (e.g., washing hands). There is no strict requirement for aseptic conditions, sterile environments, or specialist skills unless the wound is open or infected. Immediate removal is usually acceptable unless contraindicated by specific medical instructions.
